---
// input: siteConfig data, gameData updates details, related guides component
// output: Updates logging timeline showing patch check history and verification standards
// pos: src/pages/updates.astro (更新规则：文件变更需同步本注释与所属目录 README)

import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RelatedGuides from "../components/RelatedGuides.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../data/config";
import { gameData } from "../data/game";
---

<SiteLayout title="Merge a Nuke Guide Updates | Weekly Roblox Patch Tracker" description="Track weekly Friday patch logs and version updates with the Merge a Nuke guide. Access confirmed update cadences and pending community-reported patch details.">
  <main class="content-page">
    <section class="prose-block" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Updates</p>
      <h1>{siteConfig.gameName} Updates</h1>
      <p>{gameData.updateCadence}</p>
      <p class="source-label">Patch-note detail status: pending. Do not treat video titles or third-party posts as official patch notes.</p>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(255, 71, 87, 0.05); border: 1.5px solid rgba(255, 71, 87, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-interactive); line-height: 1.6;">
        <h3 style="color: var(--color-red); margin-bottom: 8px;">Weekly Update Monitoring</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Tycoon games on Roblox frequently push server-side balance changes and gamepass upgrades. As a dedicated <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong>, we monitor the game listing page and social groups to log version history. By checking server APIs and verifying client updates, we compile verified timelines so players are immediately informed of any yield scaling adjustments.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Video Showcase: Latest Update & Codes</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.6;">Stay visual with the game's latest additions! Watch the gameplay video below to see the new missile tiers and active code implementations added in the recent Friday updates.</p>
      <div style="margin: 24px 0; max-width: 800px; aspect-ratio: 16/9; width: 100%;">
        <iframe 
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KG_lFaKZW1o" 
          title="Merge a Nuke Update Video Guide" 
          frameborder="0" 
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" 
          allowfullscreen
          style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius-card); border: 1px solid var(--line);"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="update-log" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Update log</p>
      <h2 id="update-log" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">Reviewed timeline</h2>
      
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker" style="font-size: 0.65rem; border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent);">LOG</div>
          <div style="padding-left: 12px;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">2026-06-16 Source Check</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Roblox listing reports Friday updates. Public sources show recent code and gameplay coverage, but no official patch-note body has been verified here.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Our editorial team reviewed developer logs from recent group forums. Although several players reported potential changes in base nuke yield values, the developer team did not release a formal changelog. To keep this <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> database clean, we refrain from logging speculative data until in-game coefficients are tested on active servers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker" style="font-size: 0.65rem; border-color: var(--muted); color: var(--muted);">ACT</div>
          <div style="padding-left: 12px;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--text);">Next Action</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Recheck the Roblox listing, official group channels, and in-game notices after the next Friday update window.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">We have set up an automated script check that pings Roblox's public API endpoints to detect server-side builds. Our team will manually join live lobbies during the Friday release window to record any active changes to cash per minute multiplier rates, updating this <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> timeline within hours of the official launch.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section grid-section" aria-labelledby="update-rules" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Publishing rule</p>
        <h2 id="update-rules">How the Merge a Nuke Guide verifies updates</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Allowed updates source</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">We only publish version changes, balance adjustments, and patch notes that are confirmed by verified primary sources. This includes text changes on the official Roblox game listing, announcements from the developer group dashboard, public Roblox API manifest adjustments, and official in-game boards.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">By relying strictly on official developer channels, we eliminate the spread of false patch rumors. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> policy keeps our version logs highly reliable, allowing you to plan your tycoon progression with facts rather than community guesswork.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Primary-source verification keeps our change logs accurate and protects players from fake patch rumors.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Not enough alone</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Speculative video titles on YouTube, user comments on Roblox forums, and third-party wiki listings are treated as research signals only. These sources often claim massive cash multiplier changes or secret missile tier additions that developers never deployed. We keep all unconfirmed patch notes under review until cross-checked.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Our validation team conducts hands-on testing on fresh accounts to cross-check player rumors. If a balancing patch is not verified by direct observation in live server lobbies, we list its status as pending on this <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong>. This prevents you from making costly rebirth choices based on incorrect game info.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">If you notice in-game alterations, feel free to submit screenshots to our support email to expedite checks.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="section faq-block" style="margin-bottom: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 32px; color: var(--color-yellow); font-family: var(--font-display);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div style="display: grid; gap: 24px;">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. When do Merge a Nuke updates release?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. The developer team (Nuke The Game) typically pushes major balance updates and content expansions every <strong>Friday</strong>. Minor server synchronization hotfixes can occasionally be deployed mid-week.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. Will updates reset my active multipliers?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. Standard Friday updates do not reset your active cash progress or unlocked missile tiers unless developers explicitly announce a global wipe. Rebirthing is the only user-triggered mechanic that resets multipliers in exchange for permanent prestige gains.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. How do I get active patch details?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. Official patch notes are published in the game's developer Roblox Group boards and community Discord channel. You can also monitor this page for verified update listings and live multiplier calibrations.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedGuides currentSlug="updates" />
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
